Gooey Butter Cake Bars
  --Cook's Country

Crust:
2 1/2 c (12 1/2 oz) ap flour
3/4 c (3 oz) confectioners' sugar
3/4 tsp salt
12 tbsp unsalted butter, melted

Adjust oven rack to upper middle position and heat oven to 350F. Make foil sling for 13x9" baking pan (do not use glass or ceramic). Combine flour, sugar, and salt in bowl. Add butter and stir with rubber spatula until evenly moistened. Crumble dough over bottom of prepared pan. Using bottom of dry measuring cup, press dough into even layer. Using fork, dock dough ~20 times. Bake until edges are light golden brown, ~20 min. Transfer pan to wire rack and let cool completely, ~30 min. 

Filling:
8 oz cream cheese, softened
8 tbsp unsalted butter, softened
4 c (1 lb) confectioners' sugar + extra for dusting
2 large eggs + 2 yolks
2 tbsp vanilla
1/4 tsp salt

Combine cream cheese and butter in bowl of stand mixer fitted with paddle. With mixer running on low speed, slowly add usgar and mix until fully combined, ~1 min, scraping down sides and bottom of bowl as needed. Increase speed to medium high and mix until light and fluffy, ~2 min (mix should  have consistency of frosting). Spread filling evenly over cooled crust. Tap pan gently on counter to release air bubbles. Bake until top is golden brown, edges have cracked, and center jiggles slightly when pan is gently shaken, ~30 min. Transfer pan to wire rack and let cool completely, at least 3 hrs. Using foil sling, lift out of pan. cut into 12 pieces and dust with extra sugar. Can be stored in airtight container at room temp for up to 3 days.


Notes: This recipe uses a whole 2 lb bag of confectioners' sugar
